# Viewer Action Menu Refactor

- Prefer shared action primitives for repeated viewer chrome controls:
  - `src/viewer/react/components/common/IconButton.jsx` for icon-only buttons with tooltip, disabled, copied, and pressed state.
  - `src/viewer/react/components/common/ActionMenu.jsx` for trigger/menu-item structure.
  - `src/viewer/react/hooks/useDismissableLayer.js` for outside click and Escape dismissal.
- Dismiss behavior must be Shadow DOM-safe:
  - Use `event.composedPath()` when available.
  - Attach listeners through the element root from `getRootNode()` and the owning document when needed.
  - Clean up listeners from React effects.
- Preserve existing class names unless intentionally migrating styles in the same patch. Avoid redesigning floating actions, explorer row menus, or toolbar spacing during behavior extraction.
- Keep React components declarative. Components should describe buttons, menu items, and callbacks; browser side effects belong in viewer action/helper modules.
- Browser operations such as opening tabs, copying links, printing, and exporting should stay under `src/viewer/actions/` or focused helper modules rather than being implemented inline in row/header components.
